The paper deals with the analysis of the sequential Rademacher complexity, which is a common tool in machine learning and statistical learning theory. The paper also uses concepts from sublinear expectation theory, which is a relatively new area of research in probability theory and has applications in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.PR (Probability), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
